items.text:
Casting Call: The Chaos

We are seeking talented and passionate actors (18+) to join our exciting new Indie project! This is a unique opportunity to be part of a creative and collaborative production, utilizing **virtual production techniques** and **green screen technology**.

Requirements:

- Must be 18 years or older

- Comfortable performing in front of a green screen

- Enthusiastic about participating in an indie, creative-driven environment

Details:

- This is an unpaid project, but it offers a great chance to build your portfolio and gain experience in virtual production.

- Flexible scheduling for green screen scenes.

- A fantastic opportunity to work with a dedicated team on a passion project.

-IMDb Credit

If you're excited to bring unique characters to life in an innovative way, we'd love to hear from you!

To Apply:

Please submit a headshot, resume, and a brief video introduction.

They do not have to be professional!

We are looking for someone to portray these characters!

More information will be given after submission:

Chris presents himself as calm, confident, and even comforting. His tone is measured — he doesn’t command; he invites. He speaks like a leader or preacher, someone used to controlling a room through subtle persuasion rather than force. The steady eyes, careful pouring, and soft assurances suggest someone who knows how to perform sincerity.

Underneath the calm surface, there’s a manipulative intent.

Chris Myers (African American ages 20-30)

https://form.jotform.com/250471188877166

items.text:
Casting Call – Female “Therapist” Role (Paid, London – Sun 26th Oct)

Looking for an older female actor (age 40+) to play a therapist in a comedic livestream segment with a streamer and a rapper.

Details:
Date: Sunday 26th October
Time: 1-hour session (exact time TBC – evening)
Location: London
Pay: £100 + travel (same-day payment)

Role:
You’ll play a bold, outgoing therapist leading a mock therapy session with the rapper. The entire bit is improvised, so you’ll need to think on your feet — asking sharp, funny, and probing questions to get the “patient” talking, while keeping it entertaining and believable.

No script — just confident, natural improv. The vibe is smart, witty, and lighthearted rather than serious.

Requirements:
 • Female, 40+
 • Strong improv skills and quick reactions
 • Outgoing personality and confident on camera
 • Comfortable performing in a live setting
 • Based in or able to travel to London

If you’re interested, please DM me with your name, age, photo, and a short note about your acting or improv experience.

items.text:
🎬 Casting Call: What Remains (Short Film)
Genre: Drama / Psychological Thriller
Location: To be chosen 2 hours at max away from bath area, EXT filming
Shooting Dates: 12-13th Nov or 19th-20th Nov
Director: Ryan Hurley
Writer: Peter Ferris
Compensation: Unpaid / Expenses Covered / Meals Provided
📖 Synopsis
What Remains is a short psychological folk-horror film about two exiled siblings struggling to survive in the wilderness. As starvation sets in, the older sister, begins to sense something moving in the woods, a presence whispering to her through the wind. When her younger brother weakens, those whispers turn into temptation, promising salvation through sin. In a moment of desperation, she discovers the truth: the spirit isn’t hunting them - it’s inside her.
A haunting story about faith, hunger, and the monstrous things love can become when survival is all that’s left.
🎭 Roles

items.summary:
🎬 Casting Call: What Remains (Short Film)
Genre: Drama / Psychological Thriller
Location: To be chosen 2 hours at max away from bath area, EXT filming
Shooting Dates: 12-13th Nov or 19th-20th Nov
Director: Ryan Hurley
Writer: Peter Ferris
Compensation: Unpaid / Expenses Covered / Meals Provided
📖 Synopsis
What Remains is a short psychological folk-horror film about two exiled siblings struggling to survive in the wilderness. As starvation sets in, the older sister, begins to sense something moving in the woods, a presence whispering to her through the wind. When her younger brother weakens, those whispers turn into temptation, promising salvation through sin. In a moment of desperation, she discovers the truth: the spirit isn’t hunting them - it’s inside her.
A haunting story about faith, hunger, and the monstrous things love can become when survival is all that’s left.
🎭 Roles
1.Elle- Early 20's
2.Samuel- Mid to late teens
 
🎥 Audition Details

Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 43/2025

DIE NEUE SAISON DES EU XXL WANDERKINOS STARTET UND KÜRBISTIME IN DER MOVIETIME 

Bald heisst es wieder "Süsses oder Saures" und passend zum Start von Halloween startet gleich in mehreren Kooperationskinos BLACK PHONE 2.

Zur neuen Saison der EUXXL Reihe sprachen wir mit Annemarie Maurer, die in Wullersdorf diese Eventreihe betreut.

Roland Kaiser und Bruce Springsteen sind nicht nur auf der Bühne anzutreffen, nein ab sofort gibt es die beiden auch in den Kinos zu sehen und zu hören.

Weitere Filmtipps und Musik in Memoriam Diane Keaton  präsentiert Ihnen Sarah Fuchs.

Mittwoch 22.10.25 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

message.text: Immer wieder stehen für  einige mir bekannten, befreundeten Musiker und Kunst schaffenden plötzlich  die kreativen Zeiger still. Idole und Künstler unserer Jugend, gehören auf einmal zur Geschichte. Mit Wolke7 habe ich für mich einen Weg gefunden, meine Trauer über diese Verluste, der fehlenden  Menschen, zu bewältigen. Wenn ich damit auch anderen diesen schönen Gedanken vermitteln kann, ist es doch ok.

# Improvised Filmmaking Workshop in Berlin
## One week to go!

Actors & Directors: Ready to create powerful scenes spontaneously? ✨

Explore the magic of actor-director collaboration in our **Improvised Filmmaking Workshop**.

This hands-on weekend intensive is for all levels. We’ll explore the creation of compelling stories together, building trust, and finding freedom in your craft.

## 🗓️ **UPCOMING DATES:**
* Nov 1/2: **Only three spots left**
* Nov 15/16
* Dec 6/7

## **THE LOWDOWN:**

🎬 For Actors & Directors (all levels)

🇬🇧  In English

⏰ Sat & Sun, 10:00 – 19:00

📍 Reflektor Neukölln

Read what past participants have to say: reviews available on my website!

Don't miss out.

#FilmmakingWorkshop #ActorWorkshop #DirectorWorkshop #ImprovisedFilmmaking #BerlinCreatives #BerlinFilm #BerlinActors #BerlinDirectors #Neukölln #ReflektorNeukölln #WorkshopBerlin #IndieFilmmaking #Improv #SceneStudy #Collaboration

The Pull | Short Film is looking for background actors.

Male & Female, age range 18-70.

Role as passionate spectators in a tug of war match.

Shooting Dates: 30th Oct morning (about 4 hours)

ACHTUNG ACHTUNG! 🐟 🌊 

Für das Projekt "FISHING FLIES" der Masterklasse Film & TV der FH St. Pölten suchen wir ab sofort nach drei Schauspieler*innen, die dem Film mit ihrer Präsenz ein wenig Leben einhauchen wollen😊 

**HARD FACTS:**
* Absurder Kurzfilm
* 6 Drehtage Anfang Jänner 2026
## **3 Schauspieler:innnen gesucht**
* Für ILSEBILL: Frau, 40 - 60 J. (ab 1,70m)
* Für MENNO: Mann, 20 - 30 J. (bis 1,70m)
* Für WILMUR BUTT: Mann, 40 - 60 J.

**DIE ROLLEN:**
* **Unsere erste Rolle ist "ILSEBILL".** 
Für unsere kampflustige Wissenschaftlerin suchen wir eine Frau im Alter von 40-60 Jahren und einer Größe ab 1,70m. 🧳🕹 

* **"MENNO" ist unsere nächste Rolle, die es zu **besetzen gilt! 
Für unseren impulsiven Agenten suchen wir nach einem Schauspieler im Alter von 20-30 Jahren und mit einer Größe bis 1,70m! 🕴🔎 

* **Und zu guter Letzt: "WILMUR BUTT"! **
Für unseren skurrilen "Fischbringer" suchen wir nach einem Schauspieler im Alter von 40-60 Jahren. 🐟💎 

Schreibt uns gerne direkt hier auf Facebook, an fishingflies.production@gmail.com oder meldet euch direkt bei unserem Casting-Team unter der Nummer +43 680 311 0685!  

Fish Out!🐟

items.text:
Casting Call 📣 

Wir suchen die Gesichter für unsere Haupt- und Nebenrollen! Du findest, du passt perfekt zu einer dieser Figuren? Dann melde dich bei uns! Ganz einfach via Mail deine Bewerbung an casting@datingoffline.de senden 📨 

Drehzeitraum wird zwischen dem 24.11 und 05.12 sein (genauere Infos folgen), gedreht wird in Wiesbaden/Frankfurt und Umgebung 🎥

Wir sind ein junges und motiviertes Team, das Lust auf eine erfolgreiche und unvergessliche Zeit am Set haben - wir freuen uns, dich dabei zu haben! 

Findet mehr auf Instagram:
https://www.instagram.com/datingoffline.shortfilm?igsh=MWE2ZHE5aGdhNThsaQ%3D%3D&utm_source=qr

Casting Call 📣 

Wir suchen die Gesichter für unsere Haupt- und Nebenrollen! Du findest, du passt perfekt zu einer dieser Figuren? Dann melde dich bei uns! Ganz einfach via Mail deine Bewerbung an casting@datingoffline.de senden 📨 

Drehzeitraum wird zwischen dem 24.11 und 05.12 sein (genauere Infos folgen), gedreht wird in Wiesbaden/Frankfurt und Umgebung 🎥

Wir sind ein junges und motiviertes Team, das Lust auf eine erfolgreiche und unvergessliche Zeit am Set haben - wir freuen uns, dich dabei zu haben! 

Findet mehr auf Instagram:
https://www.instagram.com/datingoffline.shortfilm?igsh=MWE2ZHE5aGdhNThsaQ%3D%3D&utm_source=qr

items.text:
Hello everyone,

My name is Kayuran and I’m currently working on my first short mobile horror film. The script is in progress, and I’m looking for passionate people who would like to join me on this creative journey.

I’m specifically looking for:
🎬 A professional film editor
🎥 A camera operator (based in Durban/Chatsworth area)

The goal is to work together as a team and create something special. This project isn’t about making money — it’s about sharing stories and giving audiences an enjoyable and memorable film experience.

If you’re interested in being part of this project or know someone who might be, please feel free to reach out. Let’s build something amazing together!

From 
KM PICTURE

items.text:
**MSP SØGER 2 SKUESPILLERE (ULØNNET)**

Kære alle! Vi er et hold fra Multiplatform Storytelling and Production (MSP) i Aarhus, og skal i gang med en kort 1 dags produktion, stilet efter HBO’s “The Outsider”.

📌 **Logline**

*En lille dreng er blevet brutalt myrdet, og en efterforskningsleder forsøger at presse svar ud af det eneste vidne. *

Produktionen indebærer to korte scener; en forhørsscene, og en scene i skoven, dagen hvor liget blev fundet. 

Til dette projekt leder vi efter følgende. Køn og alder er underordnet, om du er 20 eller 60, så send en mail:
* **Detektiven** - mørk sindet noir-type, og lederen af efterforskningen. 
* **Vidnet** - forskræmt hunde gænger og personen der fandt liget. 

**Optagelser foregår Mandag d. 27. oktober.**

📅Tidspunktet vil være mellem 9 til 17.

📍 Alle optagelser vil foregå i Aarhus. 

Der vil være forsyninger og forplejning på set, naturligvis. 

Hvis det vækker interesse for jer, så kontakt mig, Harald Ruby (producer) på:
* [MkuuAngel@gmail.com](mailto:MkuuAngel@gmail.com)
* +45 42491424

Send jeres navn, alder, vellignende billeder, samt evt. erfaring (erfaring ikke påkrævet). 

Vi håber meget I vil være med!

Harald Ruby, Anna Brahe, Anja Skov, Laurits Klinke, Valdemar Hauritz, og Victor Panduro.

SINGING LESSONS £60 hour

**First Session £10! **

- West End credited performer with 4 University degrees in teaching and voice and music. YOUR LIE IN APRIL, FROZEN, CYRANO DE BERGERAC, EVITA, THE KING AND I.

-Teaching in London out of Dance Attic Studios Fulham Broadway @danceatticstudios and ONLINE.

- Got recurring technical problems? Have you ever been told that certain genres and songs are just not for you? That your voice will always be a certain way? Have you ever left a singing lesson confused?

- Join the hundreds who have deliberately and conscientiously tackled their technique, and start building confidence today.

- Clients tend to have graduated from 3 year programs and leave with fundamental holes in their technique that they now want to fill. Is that you?

BOOK at www.chrisfung.co.uk

Chris Fung - Singing Teacher

CASTING CALL FOR A STUDENT SHORT-FILM!

Hi hi! My name is Megan Veto and I am a student at the Aurora Community College and will serve as the Writer/Director of this project. I am in need of actors/actresses for my Production 1 project! This will be unpaid, though I will provide anyone interested with a final version of the film. You will also be fed, so please let me know of any allergies or specific diets you may have!

Title: On the Rocks
Genre: Romantic Comedy
Logline: An angry bride walks into a bar and shakes up Ramos’s day.

SHOOTING DAYS: November 8th (10a - 6p) - 9th (1p - 7p)

LOCATION: 9075 E Lowry Blvd Denver, CO 80230

CHARACTERS:

-Ramos: The bartender. Late 20’s - early 30’s. Calm, cool, and collected. Takes care of his patrons. Wardrobe will be all black and a black button-up shirt.

-Sarah: The angry bride. Mid - late 20’s. Feisty, knows what she wants, but eventually softens under Ramos’s care. Please let me know what your dress size is so I can find a bride’s dress that fits! 😁

-Mike: The ex. Mid - 20’s. Flustered, desperately looking for Sarah. Cheated. Wardrobe will be black slacks and a nice white button-down shirt.

-Ruth: Sarah’s mom. 50’s. Helps Mike look for Sarah. Wardrobe will be a nice dress.

Please email me at megveto96@gmail.com with your headshot and demo reel, I will send you the script to read over.

Thank you so muc

items.text:
Genre: Romance/Drama

Logline: Soulmates bound from the beginning of time must navigate the blurred lines between dreams and reality to discover their destiny together.

Roles:

Atlas: 20s, Male

Atlas always feels the weight of the world on his shoulders. He understands more about life and the universe than most people, which doesn’t help his abilities to strike up a conversation and ends up making him look reserved and detached. Atlas feels everything from the rotation of the Earth to everything that is supposed to happen in the future. His connection with the world makes him patient, almost seeming like he is unable to act on his desires, because he knows what the future holds.

Luna: 20s, Female

Luna enjoys the complexities of figuring out what life is. She wants to follow her passions and figure out what they mean along the way. She isn’t the type to turn people away, but instead see what they change in her life. She is never afraid, takes her own mortality in her hands, and believes there is a right answer to everything. The spark of life is in her and she doesn’t want to let anything snuff it out. Her dreams start to show her the past and what the future holds for her.

Pierce: 20s, Male

Pierce is a constant. He is dating Luna. He never does anything unexpected. He has a very simplistic view of the world and events that occur outside of it don’t really concern him. He is steadfast in his decisions and never doubts who he is or what he is doing. You can always expect him to be around, but if things get deeper he will very quickly drown from the weight of his inexperience.

Production Company: pearscarfproductions

Writer/Director: Nathan Chelf

Cinematographer: Nate Coberly

Production Type: Independant

Contact Info: pearscarfproductions@gmail.com

Run Time: Short Film

Compensation: Negotiable, this is a low budget, self funded project.

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: We will be holding in person auditions this Saturday, October 25th from 9:00 AM until 2:00 PM at 3111 E Colfax Ave Denver, CO 80206. Please email us if you are interested and we will get you a time slot. If you are unable to make it in person please reach out and we will set up a virtual audition another time or send you information to do a self tape. For in person we would love to see a monologue and we will have you do cold readings from the script.

Shooting Schedule: We are planning to be filming in December, final dates will be confirmed based on the schedules of our cast.

Filming Locations: The Denver Metro Area

Thank you for taking the time to read through this and I hope to hear from you soon!

 So I like to think I can give a little Kick, and a little spice or flavor to any role you might have in mind.

 Would love to work with you. Can't wait to see you on set. Available and ready to work. Reel Credit: Produced by Sunny Creative Sunny Creative, Van Nuys, CA . 

RJ Castro

# (Paid) Casting for George Fox University Student Film, (Hillsboro, Oregon)

We are a group of George Fox students shooting a short film at the Airplane Home for our Location Production class, looking for a total of three non-union actors.

Project Title: Clearing The Air

Location: Airplane Home: 15270 SW Holly Hill Rd, Hillsboro, OR 97123

Safety Considerations: Dress for potential rain and cold weather. Several cats roam around the area, so be weary if you have any allergies. The actor that plays Jean will hold a non functional prop firearm.

 Shoot Dates: 10/28/2025 and 10/30/2025, 2:00PM - 9:00PM

Age Requirement: 18 and over

Pay: 50$ per day

You will receive a collection of your scenes to include in your reel.

Synopsis: Lost in the woods, siblings Gertie and Hudson come upon an airplane containing valuables. The sister aims to ransack the plane, while her brother urges her against it. Upon the return of the airplane’s resident, Jean, the sister attempts to escape with her spoils by attacking Jean from behind while her brother serves as a distraction. Her plan is thwarted by Jean, who catches her in the act, and Hudson, who reveals her presence and forces her to return what she stole. Once the two parties agree to part ways, it is revealed that Jean is a fugitive with a reward for her capture, worth more than anything the siblings could’ve stolen.

Character Breakdown

(Antagonist) Jean: A perceptive older woman with a soft face but a hardened demeanor, a criminal past, and a lifetime of secrets behind her eyes.

Age: The character is meant to be in her early sixties, but her age isn't a strict guideline.

(Protagonist) Hudson: A thoughtful late teen with dark hair, an anxious posture, and a subdued retro rock styling, who has a tendency to let others walk over him.

He is the younger brother to Gertie.

"Think William Miller in Almost Famous but more frazzled and sarcastic."

Age: Roughly 18-19

(Protagonist) Gertie: An outdoorsy, has-it-all-together college girl with a “Karen Carpenter” fashion sense, a hidden impulsive nature, and a proclivity toward not seeing beyond her own scope.

Age: Around 20-21 years old

Audition sides are in the link below. Please record your auditions and send them to Bronson Revilla at brevilla21@georgefox.edu.

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing)

items.text:
**CASTING CALL – Gaunt Man / Doctor (Dual Role) in Short Film *****The Damned Spot***

**Production Title:** *The Damned Spot*
**Company:** SWRCO Studios / Racetothefinishline Studios
**Location:** Atlanta, GA
**Union Status:** Non-Union
**Compensation:** $200 flat rate (2 half-days)
**Role: Gaunt Man / Doctor (Male, 40s–80s)**

**Character Description:**
This is a dual-performance role. The **Doctor** appears grounded, calm, and professional — a clinician trying to reassure his patient. The **Gaunt Man** is his nightmarish double: unsettling, skeletal in presence, and haunting. The shift between the two is central to the film’s psychological horror.

**Requirements:**
* Male, age range 40–85
* Ability to portray both a grounded, realistic character and a chilling, silent presence
* Strong facial expression and physical control — much of the horror relies on stillness and presence
* Comfortable with light makeup (pale complexion, under-eye work) and basic VFX markers
**Filming Commitment:**
* 2 Half-Days
* $200 flat rate
**To Apply:**

Please submit:
* Headshot and resume (or reel, if available)
* Brief note about prior experience in psychological drama or horror
* Contact information

Send submissions to: **studio@swrco.us**
**Deadline:** **10-24-2025**

**Requirements:**
* Male, age range 40–85
* Ability to portray both a grounded, realistic character and a chilling, silent presence
* Strong facial expression and physical control — much of the horror relies on stillness and presence
* Comfortable with light makeup (pale complexion, under-eye work) and basic VFX markers
**Filming Commitment:**
* 2 Half-Days
* $200 flat rate
**To Apply:**

Please submit:
* Headshot and resume (or reel, if available)
* Brief note about prior experience in psychological drama or horror
* Contact information

Send submissions to: **studio@swrco.us**
**Deadline:** **10-24-2025**

STUDENT FILM, SHOOTING IN MANCHESTER, EARLY NOV, UNPAID

THE INTERROGATOR

mid 30s. 

Stoic but becomes fascinated with the two thieves' stories. 

RAY

20 - 30

NICK

18 - 25

new to the crime world, scruffy and erratic. Intimidated by Ray.

We are currently looking for self tape auditions

If interested please message me here or email izzyhambury1@gmail.com

for further details

Get ready for the Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event happening on Sunday, 26th October! 

 

**📍 𝐋𝐨𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧:** HOME Mcr, 𝟐 𝐓𝐨𝐧𝐲 𝐖𝐢𝐥𝐬𝐨𝐧 𝐏𝐥, 𝐌𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐡𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐌𝟏𝟓 𝟒𝐅𝐍 

**🕑 𝐓𝐢𝐦𝐞:** 𝟐:𝟎𝟎 𝐩.𝐦. - 𝟔:𝟑𝟎 𝐩.𝐦. 

 

This is not just another event; it’s your chance to connect with a dynamic community of actors, directors, producers, and writers who share your passion!
Networking is an essential part of our industry, so don’t let this opportunity pass you by.
Tickets are available at this link. 

[https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239](https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239)

 

Get ready to immerse yourself in a space filled with talented actors, visionary directors, influential producers, and skilled crew members, all eager to forge meaningful connections and who could help bring your next big project to life.

 

Also, if you're looking for captivating headshots or seeking to refresh your current images, the excellent Lisa Barton from Lisa Barton photography will be joining us at the event to showcase her incredible work!
Don’t miss out—make sure to stop by and connect with her!

 

Come and join us, we can’t wait to meet you 🌟

**📍 𝐋𝐨𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧:** HOME Mcr, 𝟐 𝐓𝐨𝐧𝐲 𝐖𝐢𝐥𝐬𝐨𝐧 𝐏𝐥, 𝐌𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐡𝐞𝐬𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐌𝟏𝟓 𝟒𝐅𝐍 

**🕑 𝐓𝐢𝐦𝐞:** 𝟐:𝟎𝟎 𝐩.𝐦. - 𝟔:𝟑𝟎 𝐩.𝐦. 

 

This is not just another event; it’s your chance to connect with a dynamic community of actors, directors, producers, and writers who share your passion!
Networking is an essential part of our industry, so don’t let this opportunity pass you by.
Tickets are available at this link. 

[https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239](https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239)

 

Get ready to immerse yourself in a space filled with talented actors, visionary directors, influential producers, and skilled crew members, all eager to forge meaningful connections and who could help bring your next big project to life.

 

Also, if you're looking for captivating headshots or seeking to refresh your current images, the excellent Lisa Barton from Lisa Barton photography will be joining us at the event to showcase her incredible work!
Don’t miss out—make sure to stop by and connect with her!

 

Come and join us, we can’t wait to meet you 🌟

sharedPost.text:
Angaż do sceny gwałtu.

O tym trójkącie już pisałem na początku września, ale ostatnio znowu się uaktywnił. Nie tak dawno podrabiał jeszcze agencję Kayax, a wcześniej Casting Busters i ATM. Na ten czas nadal posługuje się swoją bazą danych adresów e-mail, które zgromadził na etapie zamieszczania swoich postów, poprzez które szukał swoich ofiar. Nadal, bo widocznie powrócił do korzeni.

Nadal posługuje się jednym z nowszych adresów e-mail, którym w tym przypadku jest anna.fhz@outlook.com. Przeważnie można go spotkać w treści posta, gdzie w skrócie jest zamieszczona oferta, wymagania oraz wytyczne. Jednym z nich swojego czasu był link do profilu, który już nie istnieje. W tej chwili wygląda to tak:

1. Post z ofertą od np. Karolina Sikora

2. W treści znajduje się adres anna.fhz@outlook.com

3. Po nawiązaniu kontaktu ze wspomnianego adresu przychodzi odpowiedź, a w niej link do jednego z profili pedofila tj. https://www.facebook.com/PWyszomirski80

Ta etapowość kontaktu ma za zadanie rozwiać wątpliwości i wzbudzić zaufanie jak dla mnie. Docelowa ofiara zwraca uwagę na to, że coś się dzieje z jej ewentualnym angażem. Dostała się. Kolejno otrzymuje na swój adres pliki, gdzie jest zarys fabuły i postaci. Ostatnio znalazły się tam nawet zdjęcia z AI. Kolejno rozmawia się poprzez messengera z Pawłem Wyszomirskim. Prosi o jej zdjęcia, a dla niepoznaki takie, o które normalnie by prosił, gdyby był to realny casting. To emocje takie jak strach, złość i radość. Kolejno prosi o zdjęcia normalne w ubraniu, a później już w bieliźnie lub czymś obcisłym. Po drodze pyta o wymiary, doświadczenie i prowadzi rozmowę nie wzbudzając podejrzeń. W końcu prosi o zdjęcie piersi, a potem w ogóle nagie. Każdorazowo chwali małoletnią i to emocjonalnie. Nagradza ją tym.

Gdy docelowa ofiara protestuje przed tym ostatnim etapem, ten wspomina, że przecież czytała zarys fabuły, a tam była informacja o prawdziwym gwałcie. Z resztą część z fabułą tak naprawdę pojawia się w wiadomości z messengera, ale w natłoku wymiany zdań po prostu umyka. Pedofil wywołuje zażenowanie o małoletniej, gdyż powołuje się na to, że skoro czytała, to chyba wie? Tutaj następuje wejście na jej dorosłość, ambicje i konsekwencje wyboru. Gdy wysyła takowe zdjęcie … przegrywa.

Pedofil przeważnie jest blokowany, ale ma przecież adres e-mail, numer telefonu, a czasem i adres zamieszkania. Pisze do swojej ofiary, a gdy ta ulegnie, to już nie ma końca. Ze swojej strony wtedy zalecam zarchiwizowanie wszelkich danych z komunikatora, skrzynki @ i ewentualnych pobocznych informacji. Dalej dobrze jest skasować konto na FB, @ oraz zrobić nowy numer. Dlaczego? Negatywny bohater potrafi odezwać się po jakimś czasie i po chwili względnego spokoju, szantażem doprowadzić do podobnej sytuacji. Te dane, która ofiara powinna skasować umożliwiają mu jej odnalezienie. Wtedy także proponuję udać się na najbliższy komisariat w celu złożenia zawiadomienia. Przed tą wizytą lepiej przygotować się merytorycznie i  np. spisać wszystko to, co się pamięta i w postaci wydruków dołączyć do zeznań.

Wracając do fejkowych kont Robercika to ma ich trzy, z których tylko jedno nie ma linku spersonalizowanego:

Wiktoria Miłek

https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100069643696924

Paweł Wyszomirski

https://www.facebook.com/PWyszomirski80

https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100064192556671

Karolina Sikora

https://www.facebook.com/karolina.sikora.9212

https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100015721597941

Pedofil ten zawsze powołuje się na produkcje Netflixa, a raz zrobił to i TVN’owi. Otóż żadna z tych korporacji nie wymaga nudesów od małoletnich, a w ich filmach nie ma scen analnego gwałtu na małoletnich.

Rozmawiaj z dziećmi. Pamiętaj, że musisz poświęcić im czas, mimo iż nie masz go dla siebie. Nie wysyłaj swoich nagich zdjęć, bo wymaga tego rola. Nie ukrywaj niczego przed tymi, którzy mogą lub powinni Ci pomóc. Kontakt ze zbokiem lepiej tez zgłoś swojemu adminowi.

# 🎵 **Individuelle Software für Musiklehrer & Musikschulen – kostenlos entwickeln lassen!**

Hi, ich bin **Emanuel** und entwickle mit meinem Unternehmen **maßgeschneiderte Softwarelösungen** für kleine Unternehmen, Agenturen und Selbstständige – und ganz besonders für **Musiklehrer und Musikschulen**.

Ich weiß: Gerade am Anfang fehlt oft das Budget für passende Tools – deshalb **übernehme ich die Entwicklung kostenlos.**

Ob **Unterrichtsplanung, Terminbuchung, Schülerverwaltung, Stundenabrechnung oder Kursorganisation** – du bekommst eine Lösung, die wirklich zu **dir und deiner Schule** passt.

Du hast stattdessen eine **Idee für eine eigene Musik-App oder Lernplattform**? Auch super spannend – schreib mich gerne dafür an! 🎧

Ich übernehme die Entwicklung **kostenlos**, damit du **ohne Risiko starten** kannst.

Im Gegenzug kümmere ich mich (wenn du zufrieden bist) um **Hosting, Betreuung und Betrieb** – **fair, flexibel und bezahlbar.**

So entstehen **langfristige Partnerschaften**, die beiden Seiten etwas bringen.

Bei Interesse gerne PN :)

items.text: So here we go again for the FINAL PUSH to finish the MOST IMPORTANT BOXING MOVIE of this century, 'THE FORCE The Michael Watson Story'. First of all a HUGE thank you to all of you that came down as 'supporting artists' for our two incredible days at Longcross Studios re-creating three of the biggest fights of the golden era of boxing, you were absolutely amazing! We need your HELP again! On Saturday the 8th of November we are re-creating a huge court case at Aylesbury Crown Court (set as The Royal Courts of Justice) where Michael Watson (and team) sued The British Boxing Board of Control (BBBofC) for negligence! Then we have two more HUGE BOXING DAYS, this time at Tannery Studios in Woking on Saturday the 15th and Sunday the 16th of November where we recreate more ICONIC BOXING HISTORY. Please be aware this is an independent film so we can’t pay full SA rates so please DO NOT APPLY if that is a problem but I can guarantee you will have an unforgettable time 'literally' making history! Please email casting@magnificentfilms.co.uk if you want to come and join us on any or all of the dates? Thank you once again and I hope to see you on set!! Sean 🙏❤🎬Xx

Caped Crusader Parties is looking for new superhero and princess performers to join our growing team! If you love performing, entertaining kids and bringing big energy to events, we want to hear from you!

We’ve got lots of work coming up for the right people. We’re based mainly in London & Essex, but we deliver parties and events all over the UK. ✨

We’re proud partners of Tour International Rugby Festivals, providing character entertainment at events nationwide. 🏉
We’re also experts in children’s entertainment, trusted by families, schools and community organisations — just check our 5⭐ reviews!

✅ Great rates of pay
✅ Costumes & training provided
✅ Supportive team environment
✅ Exciting variety of events

If you’re confident, reliable, great with kids and love performing, send us a DM or call 📞 07535 822338 to apply!

Let’s make magic ✨

Casting for women who play tennis for joint pain medication advert.  Dates : Recalls 4th November Wardrobe fitting 12th or 13th November at a Location in London 
Travel 17th Nov to location in Lithuania. Shoot 18th Nov Shoot 19th Nov , Return travel to UK 20th Nov. Pay £350 per shoot day, £175 per travel day and £4,000 usage if used in the final film.  Must have valid passport. We would love to find pairs of women who play together and ideally have footage of them playing together for their self tape. If applying as a pair please send all info on one email. Please email 2 photos of you and or you and your tennis partner to hello@casscasting.com someone from the team will be in touch if they would like to request a self tape from you. Thank you.

✨ Winter Whispers – A Creative Social Evening in London ❄️

As winter settles in, let’s gather where creativity meets connection. Join SHY Films for Winter Whispers at Karma Sanctum Soho, London, on Tuesday, 11th November 2025 (6:00 PM – 10:00 PM GMT).

🎬 Whether you’re an actor, filmmaker, writer, director, producer, editor, or creative dreamer, this evening is your chance to network, pitch ideas, and be inspired by London’s vibrant creative community — all in a warm, intimate setting.

🎵 Evening Highlights:
✨ Live Winter Soundscapes – Feel the magic of the season through live music and soothing performances.
🎙️ Creative Conversations Panel – Hear from talented voices across film, TV & music.
🎤 Pitch & Connect – Step up, share your project, or simply introduce yourself to future collaborators.

🍷 Agenda:
6:00 – Networking & Drinks
7:00 – Live Music
8:00 – Pitch & Connect
9:00 – Creative Voices Panel & Q&A

✨ Come for the art. Stay for the stories. Leave inspired.

items.text:
Want to learn how to transition from doing music into Acting?
Or how to get your music in TV and Film? 

BBR Indie Films is thrilled to announce our Celebrity Guest  Panelist- Gary "LIL G" Jenkins! 

​Gary "LIL G" is a National Platinum Recording Artist (lead singer of the R&B super-group SILK), Producer, Songwriter, and Actor.

​His impressive acting credits include:
🎬 Madea's Family Reunion (Stage Play)
🎬 Sleepy Hollow
🎬 Christmas Bae (coming soon)

​Don't miss the chance to hear from a true industry veteran at our next event, we are giving all the tea. Come ready to network, we ALWAYS have several Music Supervisors in the house.

​📅 Wed, October 29th, 2025
📍 Studio Movie Grill - Marietta, GA
⏱️ 6:00 PM - 10:00 PM
👻 In the theme of Halloween. Costumes are welcomed but not required. Best Costume wins a prize. 

​Secure your tickets and learn more about BBR Indie Films at bbrindiefilms.com and on Eventbrite!

Want to learn how to transition from doing music into Acting?
Or how to get your music in TV and Film? 

BBR Indie Films is thrilled to announce our Celebrity Guest  Panelist- Gary "LIL G" Jenkins! 

​Gary "LIL G" is a National Platinum Recording Artist (lead singer of the R&B super-group SILK), Producer, Songwriter, and Actor.

​His impressive acting credits include:
🎬 Madea's Family Reunion (Stage Play)
🎬 Sleepy Hollow
🎬 Christmas Bae (coming soon)

​Don't miss the chance to hear from a true industry veteran at our next event, we are giving all the tea. Come ready to network, we ALWAYS have several Music Supervisors in the house.

​📅 Wed, October 29th, 2025
📍 Studio Movie Grill - Marietta, GA
⏱️ 6:00 PM - 10:00 PM
👻 In the theme of Halloween. Costumes are welcomed but not required. Best Costume wins a prize. 

​Secure your tickets and learn more about BBR Indie Films at bbrindiefilms.com and on Eventbrite!

PAID FEATURE ROLES

TR Castings is looking for talented individuals based in Cape Town for an upcoming film production. These are feature roles (not background).

📍 Location: Cape Town

💰 Paid Roles

🎥 Feature Characters

---

🔹 Justin

Male | 25 years old | Coloured ethnicity

Tall, lean, and strikingly handsome

🔹 Frank

Male | Early 20s | Caucasian

🔹 Garett

Male | 30–50 | South African (any race)

---

📩 To apply:

Send the following to trcastingsltd@gmail.com or WhatsApp 076 179 7034

Full name

Age

Location

Recent clear photos (headshot and full body)

Contact number

Use the role name as your subject or message title (e.g. JUSTIN – Cape Town).

---

📜 Scripts are available for each role.

If you’re interested, contact us and we’ll send you the script for your audition.

We look forward to seeing your submissions!

— TR Castings

items.text:
We’re looking for a motivated, connected, and business-minded person to help us grow TR Castings!

Your main role will be to find productions, adverts, and film projects that need extras and actors, and connect them with our agency. You’ll be paid commission for every confirmed booking or client you bring in.

✅ Work remotely / part-time

✅ No set hours

✅ Perfect for someone with contacts in film, TV, or advertising

✅ Earn per deal you bring in

If you’re confident, well-spoken, and passionate about the industry, we’d love to have you on board!

📍 Johannesburg based (but can work remotely)

📲 WhatsApp: 076 179 7034

📧 Email: [add your agency email here]

Let’s build something great together! 🎬

items.text:
Til min kortfilm Banana Ice, der er støttet af Odense Filmværksted, søger jeg to kvindelige spillere til venindeparret Rikke og Sika - spillealder 19-20.

Banana Ice handler om:

Den 18-årige Val, der i starten af historien får nedtur på efter hun, ved ankomst til baren, finder ud af at hendes veninder har ditchet hende. 

Men det bliver faktisk bare held-i-uheld, for hun ender med en aften på bar med venindeduoen Rikke og Sika.

Da de to veninder, sent på aftenen, går ud for at spice øllene op og narkopolitiet kort efter kommer ind, ender Val i et dilemma.

Hun redder hendes “nye” veninders røv, men i panik og for at redde deres egen røv, kaster Sika og Rikke hende under bussen.

Kortfilmen hedder som den gør, fordi en vape, med den smag, er gennemgående motif i historien.

Praktisk:

Kortfilmen optages i Svendborg den 29. og 30. november i dagstimerne - så der er selvfølgelig forplejning. 

Er du og måske din veninde interesseret?

Så send en mail til majamus23@gmail.com med emnet Venindeduo_BananaIce

I mailen kunne jeg godt tænke mig:

* en video af dig/jer, der som de to veninder skal få den sidste ved bordet til at købe drikkevarer til jer - det kan f.eks. være via en løgn, en leg, at stjæle eller noget helt andet.

* har du/I en showreel eller links til andet I har lavet, så send det gerne med.

* en kort, kort præsentation af dig/jer.

Her kommer lidt om veninderne:

Rikke&Sika

Sammen er de den uovervindelige venindeduo.

Man ved, ser man den ene et sted, så er den anden lige om hjørnet.

De er det kvindelige modsvar til det heteroseksuelle forholds tosomhed.

Noget både jeg og Val er misundelige på.

De er spændende og fascinerende mennesker, man ønsker at dele en aften med.

 

Sika

Hendes forældre er succesfulde, så hun kommer fra et hjem hvor der bliver forventet noget af en.

Kærligheden er ikke ubetinget, man skal præstere og gøre sig umage, før man får et klap på skulderen eller en belønning.

 

At være uartig eller opfører sig dårligt fører naturligvis til konsekvenser.

Sika finder nydelse i at være meget langt fra sine forældre, men hjemmet har klart givet hende en hårdhed.

 

Rikke

Hun har en enlig mor, inden hende og Sika blev en tosomhed, var Rikke og hendes mor det.

Hun trives godt i det kvindelige selskab og elsker fællesskab og andre menneskers samvær. Derfor former hun sig også meget efter de mennesker hun er sammen med, så hun altid passer ind og kan være en del af de sociale.

Glæder mig til at se jeres mails <33

Kh Maja, manus/instruktør

STATISTER SØGES - LØNNET (ER NU FUNDET - TAK FOR HURTIG RESPONS) 

Til optagelse på Københavns Hovedbanegård 29/10 i tidsrummet 14.30-19.00.

Make Sense søger 3-5 statister til at komme forbi og give deres umiddelbare ægte reaktioner på det man ser samt 1-2 takes med let instruktion. Der skal afsættes ca. 20-30 minutter

Formål: Kampagne/awarenessfilm til en patientforening for en alm. sygdom i Danmark.

Hvem søger vi:
* Forældre (en eller begge) med barn. Alder fra 6 år.
* Mand 45-65 år
* Kvinde +45 år

Alle former og farver er velkomne til at sende PB med lidt info om navn, alder, kontaktinfo (tlf og mail) og om man kan have barn/børn med 

DBH

Murad Ahmed

[www.makesense.dk](www.makesense.dk)

The hit Channel 4.0 entertainment show is BACK and casting for Season 2!

LOCATION: London Studio

DATES: Thursday 13th or Friday 14th November 2025

PAID

We're looking for single men (28+) and single women (25+) who want their chance to bag a date with one of the UK’s top creators.

If you’re a Confident Queen, Rizz Royalty, It Girl, Zaddie, or a Reformed F-boy, and you serve main character energy, this show wants you in the mix.

The hit Channel 4.0 entertainment show is BACK and casting for Season 2!

PAID

items.text:
Hey there! 👋🏻😃

I’m Freya Tingley — an Australian actress born and raised in Perth. I started acting at 14, taking weekly classes with a dream of one day building a career in Hollywood.

Bit by bit, I booked short films, found a local agent, and put together a demo reel — all steps that helped me make the leap to LA just before turning 18. Not long after, I landed my first major role as a series regular on Netflix’s Hemlock Grove, followed by Once Upon a Time, Jersey Boys, and DOTA: Dragon’s Blood.

Of course, it wasn’t all smooth sailing and the journey had its pitfalls and huge learning curves along the way. But those ups and the downs gave me something valuable; an understanding of what works, what doesn’t and the exact steps to take to keep moving forward. 

Most acting schools don’t teach how to build a career — they’ll say “get an agent,” or “network: it’s all about who you know!” - but there’s never a clear road map, or step-by-step plan to help you to make progress, no matter where you’re at that.

I’m building a community for actors who want a clear game plan, strategy, and support to level up and turn their goals into reality.

Come hang out with us! I’d love to meet you, hear your story, and help you move closer to your dreams.

👉 Join The Business of Acting www.skool.com/the-business-of-acting-9301/about?ref=387a46092b6b412b82c1a78a4c1a240e

See you there! 😃
— Freya

items.text:
Dream & Dazzle Parties is growing and on the lookout for more energetic, reliable, and imaginative performers to join our fun, dynamic team! We predominantly provide princess performers for children’s parties across London and surrounding areas, but we also offer other entertainment opportunities so we would love to hear from you if you meet our requirements! 🌟 

We’re especially keen to hear from people with:
🎭 Performing or teaching experience 
🎉 Experience working with children and/or leading workshops for children 
🚗 A driver’s license (a bonus but not essential)
💫 A passion for creating unforgettable memories for families

We believe kids should see performers who reflect the wonderfully diverse world they live in- so we warmly welcome applications from performers of all backgrounds, particularly those from underrepresented communities.

If you think you would make a great addition to our team, we’d love to hear from you🌟
📩 Please send your CV and a recent headshot to janelle@dreamanddazzle.co.uk

items.text:
· Title: This Side of Midnight

· Genre: Horror

· Logline: An eighteen-year-old girl must confront her inner demons, both real and metaphorical, as they test her to see if she is worthy of life itself after a brush with death.

· Role: Lilith — Female, late teens to early 20s

A newly eighteen-year-old struggling with severe depression and suicidal thoughts. Intelligent, introspective, and haunted by her inner world. The emotional core of the story.

Note: Lead role. Must be comfortable portraying intense emotional states.

Zera — Female, late teens to early 20s

Lilith’s best friend. Empathetic and determined, trying desperately to remind Lilith that she matters.

Dad — Male, 40s–50s (flexible)

A concerned father trying to reconnect with his daughter after finding her following a suicide attempt. Must convey deep emotion with subtlety.

Mom — Female, 40s–50s (flexible)

 A mother struggling to cope as her daughter begins to withdraw, stop eating, and lose hope.

Sibling — Any gender (preferably male), 10–15 (flexible)

Appears in one scene. No speaking lines, but must express strong emotion through facial expression and presence.

Cashier — Any gender/age

Background role, no speaking lines.

· Production Company: Cassidy Cheldelin — Writer, Director, Videographer, Editor
Jess Lange — Co-Director, Casting Director, Producer

· Production Type: Student Film

· Contact Information: Contact: Jess Lange — escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Instagram: @escapemind.productions 

· Run Time: Short (16 minutes)

· Compensation: Unpaid

· Union Status: Non-Union

· Audition Information: 

Format: Digital Submission

Please record a 1–2 minute monologue of your choice (preferably horror or drama) that demonstrates emotional depth. Include your name, age, preferred email & phone number, and desired role in the email. Name, age, and role for slate. 

Lilith Auditions: Monologue may be up to 5 minutes or the attached scene from the screenplay.

Dad Auditions: May choose to perform from the attached scene.

Submit to: escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Deadline: November 5, 11:59 PM (MST)

· Shooting Schedule: Mid-November (before Thanksgiving) table read, 11/8/25 at 12 (MST), location upon casting

· Filming Location: Black Forest, CO, 80908 & Colorado Springs, CO, North Academy Blvd.

· Project Description:

Two filmmakers are passionate about exploring mental health through the lens of horror. While this is not a professional production, we approach the project with deep respect and dedication to the craft. This Side of Midnight follows Lilith as she confronts her literal demons and manifestations of her struggles with mental illness, who test her will to live. When she ultimately fails, she is tragically taken, symbolizing the devastating reality of losing the battle against one’s own mind.

Lilith and Dad Scene 

Int. BEDROOM - MORNING

The screen flickers to her dad, shaking her awake

Dad

Lilith! Wake up! Please- Please, breathe please.

Lilith sits up suddenly, her breathing is chaotic, and she is in fear.

Her dad sighs in relief

Dad

Oh, thank god you are ok. I was about to call 911. What happened??

LILITH (studdering)

I- I don't know

She looks around the room, noticing the empty pill bottle next to her pillow, and she erratically shoves it further underneath so as not to let her dad see.

LILITH

Must've just been too much melatonin..

Dad

You scared the crap out of me and you're mother. Zera too.

Lilith looks defeated as her father sits more formally on her bed.

Dad

That reminds me, you should probably call her. She was worried sick about you.

LILITH

I will- I will do that.

Dad (in relief)

Good. You missed the bus. I have to go to work n' can't drive you- so have the day off.

LiLITH (under her breath)

T-Thanks.

DAD

A mental Health day- y'know? You deserve it.

Lilith's expression doesn't change. Her dad stands up and begins to put on his jacket

DAD

Let me know if you need anything, okay?

Two filmmakers are passionate about exploring mental health through the lens of horror. While this is not a professional production, we approach the project with deep respect and dedication to the craft. This Side of Midnight follows Lilith as she confronts her literal demons and manifestations of her struggles with mental illness, who test her will to live. When she ultimately fails, she is tragically taken, symbolizing the devastating reality of losing the battle against one’s own mind.

Lilith and Dad Scene 

Int. BEDROOM - MORNING

The screen flickers to her dad, shaking her awake

Dad

Lilith! Wake up! Please- Please, breathe please.

Lilith sits up suddenly, her breathing is chaotic, and she is in fear.

Her dad sighs in relief

Dad

Oh, thank god you are ok. I was about to call 911. What happened??

LILITH (studdering)

I- I don't know

She looks around the room, noticing the empty pill bottle next to her pillow, and she erratically shoves it further underneath so as not to let her dad see.

LILITH

Must've just been too much melatonin..

Dad

You scared the crap out of me and you're mother. Zera too.

Lilith looks defeated as her father sits more formally on her bed.

Dad

That reminds me, you should probably call her. She was worried sick about you.

LILITH

I will- I will do that.

Dad (in relief)

Good. You missed the bus. I have to go to work n' can't drive you- so have the day off.

LiLITH (under her breath)

T-Thanks.

DAD

A mental Health day- y'know? You deserve it.

Lilith's expression doesn't change. Her dad stands up and begins to put on his jacket

DAD

Let me know if you need anything, okay?

📸 2 STATISTER SØGES TIL FOTOOPTAGELSER I KOLDING

Pga sygdom mangler jeg 2 statister til en fotooptagelse på Comwell Kolding i morgen mandag den 20. oktober. Billederne skal bruges i markedsføringsøjemed for Comwell Hotels – primært til promovering af møder og konferencer.

Køn: Mænd og kvinder

Alder: 35 år og opefter

Hvornår: Mandag den 20. oktober 2025

Tid: Kl. 8.30–16.00

Sted: Comwell Kolding, Skovbrynet 1, 6000 Kolding

Din rolle: Mødedeltager og/eller forretningsrejsende

Dresscode: Casual business 

Forplejning: Morgenmad, frokost og eftermiddagsforplejning er inkluderet

Der vil være stylist og makeupartist til stede, som hjælper med et naturligt og professionelt look på dagen. Dog skal alle statister selv medbringe 2-3 sæt tøj jfr dresscode: Casual business.

Det er vigtigt, at du selv kan komme til og fra location, og at du selv står for transportomkostninger.

Honorar

Som tak for din medvirken modtager du et gavekort til Comwell Hotels på 1.500 kr. Bemærk, at værdien indberettes som B-indkomst til SKAT i henhold til gældende lovgivning.

Er du frisk?

så send hurtigst muligt en mail til LN@comwell.com med følgende:

• Fulde navn og kontaktoplysninger

• Alder

• Et eller flere nyere billeder i fuld profil (uden filter)

Billederne viser stemninger fra tidligere shoots og bruges kun som eksempel.

🎭 TOMORROW WE’RE BACK NEW — AND BIGGER THAN EVER! 🎭
Our sell-out new writing night Hits & Pieces returns for its 10th edition, and this one’s inspired by Seal’s iconic Kiss From a Rose! 🌹
Join us for an unforgettable evening of four completely different short plays, each written by a brilliant new voice — all inspired by the same song. Expect laughter, heartbreak, and a touch of the unexpected as every writer takes the theme in a wildly different direction.

🗓 Saturday 25th October�📍 The Old Library, New Cross�🍸 Doors 7pm for drinks, plays at 7:30pm�🎟️ Book your tickets here:

https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/hits-pieces-10-seal-tickets-1556842310259?fbclid=PAb21jcANW-3BleHRuA2FlbQIxMQABp-JI3fUVdSgsq71z9unTw9QAF5maYbsDKkCCLtkAIY1bmwmrPIcmpf4wmXQZ_aem_nXATNR7cEYS0ZsioAL4zkQ

💥 After the plays, stick around for a 90s playlist to keep the vibes going — and cast your vote live for the next song that will inspire Hits & Pieces #11!

⭐️ “Pulsing nostalgia, so ferocious that it pumps through my veins” — Theatre & Tonic�⭐️ “Every performance unveils a world of laughter, reflection, and no secrets kept” — A Young(ish) Perspective�⭐️ “Bold, bizarre, wittily written” — The Spy in the Stalls
Our Hits & Pieces nights have become a regular sell-out celebration of new writing, shining a spotlight on London’s most exciting emerging talent.

Grab your mates, grab a drink, and come be part of the story — literally. You decide what happens next.
#NewWriting #FringeTheatre #HitsAndPieces #KissFromARose #LondonTheatre #TheatreCommunity

OPEN CASTING CALL

Rose Waite Studio are looking for inter-generational pairs who share a genuine love of theatre to feature in a filmed story for The Guardian and a paid partner. You will get the chance to watch a live theatre show from the opera box at one of Lloyd Webber’s theatres.

You could be a grandparent and grandchild, friends or colleagues etc. who share a genuine love of theatre to feature in a filmed story for The Guardian and a paid partner. 

You’ll need to be based in or near London. 

This is a paid opportunity. 

If you’d like to be filmed sharing your story, email stories@rosewaite.com with details of your story together and why theatre matters to you both.

Shoot dates: 24 & 25 November

Thank you!

items.text:
Been cooking up a lot of projects behind the scenes and this is the most recent! 

Currently casting for a new short, working title 'The Heist', filming in Northern Quarter, Manchester!

In 1994, a duo of thieves, interrogated after a heist gone wrong, find their fates decided by the value of their mysterious stolen item 🪙

STUDENT FILM, SHOOTING IN MANCHESTER, EARLY NOV, UNPAID

THE INTERROGATOR

mid 30s. 

Stoic but becomes fascinated with the two thieves' stories. 

RAY

20 - 30

Confident, in charge and narcissistic. Takes the lead within the duo

NICK

18 - 25

new to the crime world, scruffy and erratic. Intimidated by Ray.

Within plenty of space to collaborate, build and bring your own energy and flair to the story and the characters, this may be a good opportunity for upcoming actors building their portfolio and looking for experience! 

We are currently looking for self tape auditions

If interested please message me here or email izzyhambury1@gmail.com

for further details

🎬 **CASTING CALL – COVENTRY UNIVERSITY FINAL YEAR FILM** 🎬

We’re currently casting for **two main characters** in our upcoming **third-year short film project**, a **horror-comedy** shooting in **Coventry** (with the possibility of additional locations — confirmed actors will be informed in advance).

📅 **Filming Period:** Mid-February to March 2026
🎞️ **Length:** Approx. 15 minutes
🎭 **Genre:** Horror Comedy

This is an **unpaid student production**, but we will **cover travel costs and catering** during filming days.

We’re looking for **dedicated and enthusiastic actors** who are passionate about working on creative projects and open to collaborating with a student film crew.

If you’re interested, please email **davist11@coventry.ac.uk** with your **headshot, showreel (if available), and a short bio**.
Once you get in touch, I’ll send over **all the details about the audition process** and what to expect.

We’re aiming to **lock in our final cast by January**, so please make sure you’re available for the filming period mentioned above.

This is a great opportunity to gain on-set experience, expand your portfolio, and be part of a fun and ambitious student film! 🎥✨

🍂I have 5 SPOTS LEFT at my **Art of Letting Go** workshop THIS SATURDAY! This is a 3-hour acting + movement workshop that helps you release the tension you’ve been carrying- in your craft, your body, and your life.

👉You do not need to be an artist to participate. If you’ve been feeling stuck, disconnected, or just ready for a reset… this is for you! It will be fun and transformative, I promise :)

💚DM me or Scan the code below, to book!

items.text:
📣🎬 CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fiancée Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22–23)
Ed’s fiancée. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Ed’s big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

# **⚔️ Soldiers – Altamont, NY (Oct 20–25)**

Hi everyone! My name is **Sarah Morgan**, and I’m a producer on the indie medieval fantasy comedy feature film ***The Kingdom of Rexmonte***. We’ll be filming in **Altamont, NY** from **October 20–25**, and we’re looking for enthusiastic volunteers to play **soldiers** in battle scenes!

 🍴 Full lunch & snacks provided
 🎭 Ren faire/medieval attire welcome
 🙌 Unpaid, but an epic film set experience!

👉 Sign up here: [[https://forms.gle/zqWmXjAw7sDqFRGv9](https://forms.gle/zqWmXjAw7sDqFRGv9)](https://forms.gle/zqWmXjAw7sDqFRGv9) 

Also, please feel free to send the flyer and Google Form around to any groups or anyone you know who may be interested. We hope to see you on set!
